<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-01T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="681" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/6: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-01T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">March 1,
                                            1919, 11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received March 1, 11.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>977. Your 888, February 26, 7 p.m. I doubt the advisability of going
                                to the expense of maintaining at the Legation an unasked for adviser
                                to the Chinese Government. Lansing.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>